le =Nancy Grace, Dean Tong | title =Breaking News Following Yesterday\u2019s Courthouse Shooting in Nevada (transcript of video) | medium =Television News | publisher =CNN | location = | date =13 June 2006 | url =http://transcripts.cnn.com/TRANSCRIPTS/0606/13/ng.01.html }}</ref> [[Expert witness|Trial Expert]]<ref name=\"SSentinelAuthorSeeks\">{{cite news | last =Work | first =Deborah | coauthors = | title =Author Seeks New Protections | newspaper =[[Sun-Sentinel]]| location = | pages = | language = | publisher = | date =7 April 1996 | url =http://articles.sun-sentinel.com/1996-04-07/lifestyle/9604070106_1_child-sexual-abuse-abuse-and-neglect-abuse-charges | accessdate =18 August 2013 }}</ref>\n| years_active              = \n| employer                  = \n| organization              = \n| agent                     = \n| known_for                 = False abuse allegation forensic expert<ref name=\"BloGTalkDiscussionTong\">{{cite news | last =Chase | first =Jennifer | coauthors = | title =Discussion with Child Abuse Expert & Forensic Consultant Dean Tong | newspaper =Blog Talk Radio| location = | pages = | language = | publisher = | date =24 February 2013 | url =http://www.blogtalkradio.com/jennifer-chase/2011/02/24/discussion-with-child-abuse-expert-forensic-consultant-dean-tong | accessdate =18 August 2013 }}</ref>\n| notable_works             = \n| style                     = \n| home_town                 = \n| salary                    = \n| net_worth                 = <!-- Net worth should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n| height                    = <!-- {{height|m=}} -->\n| weight                    = <!-- {{convert|weight in kg|kg|lb}} -->\n| television                = \n| title                     = \n| term                      = \n| predecessor               = \n| successor                 = \n| party                     = \n| movement                  = \n| opponents                 = \n| boards                    = \n| religion                  = <!-- Religion should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n| denomination              = <!-- Denomination should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n| criminal_charge           = <!-- Criminality parameters should be supported with citations from reliable sources -->\n| criminal_penalty          = \n| criminal_status           = \n| spouse                    = \n| partner                   = <!-- unmarried life partner; use ''Name (1950\u2013present)'' -->\n| children                  = \n| parents                   = \n| relatives                 = \n| callsign                  = \n| awards                    = \n| signature                 = \n| signature_alt             = \n| signature_size            = \n| module                    = \n| module2                   = \n| module3                   = \n| module4                   = \n| module5                   = \n| module6                   = \n| website                   = http://abuse-excuse.com/\n| footnotes                 = \n| box_width                 = \n}}\n\n'''Dean Tong''' is an [[United States|American]] [[author]], [[Public speaking|public speaker]], [[consultant]],<ref>{{cite news | last =Erdely | first =Sabrina Rubin | coauthors = | title =Sex Lies and Phys Ed | newspaper =Rolling Stone Magazine| location = | pages = | language = | publisher = | date =22 January 2009 | url = | accessdate = }}</ref> and trial expert in the field of false child abuse allegations.<ref name=\"CNNNancyGrace\"/><ref name=\"SSentinelAuthorSeeks\"/> He has consulted for the media on high-profile cases such as that of [[Eli\u00e1n Gonz\u00e1lez affair|Elian Gonzalez]],<ref name=\"BostonCom\">{{cite web | last =Sutton | first =Jane | authorlink = | title =Cuban Boy Faces Deep Psychological Scars | website = | publisher =Reuters| date =7 January 2000 | url =http://www.boston.com/news/daily/07/cuban_psych.htm | doi = | accessdate =18 August 2013}}</ref> [[Murder of JonBen\u00e9t Ramsey|JonBen\u00e9t Ramsey]], and [[Michael Jackson#2003\u201305: Second child sexual abuse allegations and acquittal|Michael Jackson]].<ref name=\"SoutherScribeInterview\">{{cite news | last =Tong | first =Dean | coauthors = | title =When Fatherhood Is Under Attack | newspaper =Southern Scribe| location = | pages = | language = | publisher = | date = | url =http://www.southernscribe.com/zine/culture/Tong_Dean.htm | accessdate =22 August 2013}}</ref> He is the author of three books inspired by his personal experience with being falsely accused of child abuse in 1985.<ref name=\"Channel8FFB\"/> In addition to testifying as an expert witness,<ref name=\"AberdeenNews\">{{cite news | last =Waltman | first =Scott | coauthors = | title =Judge approves defense assistance in abuse case | newspaper =Aberdeen News| location = | pages = | language = | publisher = | date =15 March 2011 | url =http://articles.aberdeennews.com/2011-03-15/news/28700712_1_richard-p-mette-abuse-related-charges-abuse-charges | accessdate =22 August 2013}}</ref> he has appeared on numerous radio talk shows and television speaking on the topic of false abuse accusations. He has also been quoted by numerous publications on the topic including by the [[Chicago Defender]],<ref>{{cite news | last =Daniels | first =Theo | title =Single Dads Exist | newspaper =Chicago Defender | date =4 July 2012 | url =http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-2721750091.html | archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20140808120354/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-2721750091.html | url-status =dead | archive-date =8 August 2014 | accessdate =18 August 2013}}</ref> [[The Virginian-Pilot]],<ref>{{cite news | last =Simpson | first =Elizabeth | title =Campaign Advocates Recognizing, Reporting Suspected Abuse | newspaper =[[The Virginian-Pilot]]| publisher =High Beam Research  | date =21 June 2007| url =http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-165367491.html | archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20140808121901/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-165367491.html | url-status =dead | archive-date =8 August 2014 | accessdate =18 August 2013 }}</ref> [[The Boston Globe]],<ref name=\"BostonCom\"/> and [[The Denver Post]].<ref>{{cite news | last =Briggs | first =Bill | coauthors = | title =Child Sex-Abuse Charges Balloon| newspaper =The Denver Post| location = | pages = | language = | publisher =  | date =26 August 1992| url = | accessdate = }}</ref>\n\n==Early life and education==\n\nTong graduated from [[Hull High School]] and later obtained a [[Bachelor of Science]] degree in Biology and Pre-Medicine from [[Northeastern University]] in 1979.<ref name=\"BostonGlobeFatherFalsely\">{{cite news | last =Carton | first =Barbara | title =A Father Falsely Accused Dean Tong Is A New Class Of Victim | newspaper =The Boston Globe| publisher =High Beam Research | date =5 April 1993 | url =http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-8221961.html | archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20121031082632/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-8221961.html | url-status =dead | archive-date =31 October 2012 | accessdate =18 August 2013 }}</ref> He went on to study at the [[University of Portsmouth|University of Portsmouth and Leeds]] in the [[United Kingdom]] where he obtained a [[Master's degree]] in Psychology and the Law in Child Forensic Studies in 2006.<ref name=\"TalkGuestDeanTong\">{{cite web|title=Dean Tong \u2013 Are you Falsely Accused of Domestic Abuse or Child Abuse? |publisher=Talk Guests |url=http://www.talkguests.com/deantong.htm |archive-url=https://archive.today/20130827223328/http://www.talkguests.com/deantong.htm |url-status=dead |archive-date=27 August 2013 |accessdate=18 August 2013 }}</ref>\n\nHis [[Thesis|Master Thesis]] at the University of Portsmouth entitled \"''Penile Plethysmograph, Abel Assessment for Sexual Interest, and MSI-II: Are They Speaking the Same Language''\" was later published in the May/June 2007 issue of The ''American Journal of Family Therapy.''<ref name=\"TalkGuestDeanTong\"/><ref>{{cite journal | last =Tong | first = Dean | authorlink = | title =The Penile Plethysmograph, Abel Assessment for Sexual Interest and MSI-II | journal =The American Journal of Family Therapy | volume = 35| issue = 3| pages = 187\u2013202| date =May\u2013June 2007 | language = | jstor = | issn = | doi =10.1080/01926180701226762 | id = | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref> He originally worked as a laboratory medical technologist prior to becoming an author and consultant.<ref name=\"BostonGlobeFatherFalsely\"/>\n\n==False allegations of abuse==\n\nIn 1985, Tong was accused by his then wife of sexually abusing his 3-year-old daughter.<ref name=\"SSentinelAuthorSeeks\"/><ref>{{cite news | last =Clark | first =Lesley | coauthors = | title =Parents Group: Restrain Power of Children\u2019s Agency | newspaper =Orlando Sentinel | location = | pages = | language = | publisher = | date =4 March 1997 | url =http://articles.orlandosentinel.com/1997-03-04/news/9703031096_1_child-abuse-bill | accessdate =22 August 2013 }}</ref> He was in a custody battle with his estranged wife at the time. While at work, Tong received a call from his attorney advising him of the allegations.<ref name=\"BostonGlobeFatherFalsely\"/> He was subsequently arrested and charged with capital sexual battery and under court order not to see his children.<ref name=\"SSentinelAuthorSeeks\"/> Tong spent two weeks in jail<ref name=\"Channel8FFB\"/> and the charges were dropped against him 14 months later for lack of evidence.<ref name=\"BostonGlobeFatherFalsely\"/> After the criminal proceedings, Tong faced ten years of legal battles including two lawsuits and spending in excess of $100,000 to clear his name.<ref name=\"SSentinelAuthorSeeks\"/>\n\n==Professional career==\n\nTong runs a consultancy in Florida by the name of ''Abuse Excuse''. He has been retained by attorneys and parents in all 50 states and has appeared on more than 2000 radio talk shows talking about false allegations of abuse.<ref name=\"BloGTalkDiscussionTong\"/> His consultancy is concentrated in the fields of divorce, child custody,  abuse accusations, sexual or physical child abuse, domestic violence, parental alienation, and sexual allegations in divorce.<ref name=\"CNNNancyGrace\"/> He has given expert testimony in 10 states in cognitive child development psychology and is contracted to perform critique of investigations conducted by [[Child Protective Services]] and law enforcement agencies related to accusations of abuse as well as forensic interviews of children allegedly abused.<ref name=\"CNNNancyGrace\"/> He has also been appointed by courts as an expert witness for criminal [[Public defender|indigent]] defendants.<ref name=\"AberdeenNews\"/> Tong has also been hired by protective mothers who lose child custody because they are perceived to be coaching their children to make false abuse allegations against fathers.<ref name=\"DrPhill\">{{cite web | last = | first = | authorlink = | title =Custody Battles | website = | publisher =Dr. Phil | date = | url =http://drphil.com/slideshows/slideshow/2008/?id=2008&slide=2&showID=377&preview=&versionID | format = | doi = | accessdate =22 August 2013}} (Slideshow of episode)</ref><ref>{{cite web | last =Fernandes | first =Gina  | authorlink = | title =Custody Crisis: Why Moms Are Punished In Court | website = | publisher =MomLogic | date =19 January 2010 | url =http://www.momlogic.com/2010/01/custody_crisis_why_mothers_are_punished_in_family_court.php | format = | doi = | accessdate =25 August 2013}}</ref>\n\nTong was part of the legal team for [[Darren Mack]] during his divorce.<ref name=\"CNNNancyGrace\"/><ref name=\"MSNBCMack\">{{cite news | last =Cosby | first =Rita | coauthors = | title =Rita Cosby Live & Direct | newspaper =Rita Cosby Live & Direct| location = | pages = | language = | publisher =MSNBC | date =14 June 2006 | url =http://www.nbcnews.com/id/13340574/ns/msnbc-rita_cosby_specials/t/rita-cosby-live-direct-june/#.Uhafsz8gi3Y | accessdate =22 August 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite book | last =Glatt | first =John | authorlink = | title =Love Her to Death | publisher =St. Martins Press | series = | volume = | edition = | year =2012 | location = | pages = | language = | url = | doi = | id = | isbn =9780312947859 | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref> Mack was later charged with the murder of his estranged wife as well as the sniper shooting of the judge who handled the divorce proceedings.<ref name=\"48hoursDarrenMack\">{{cite video | people = | title =Caught In The Crossfire | medium =Television Special | publisher =48 Hours Mystery | location = | date =24 February 2007 | url =https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=D6OyvZ3s8Y0 }}</ref> After the shooting, he spoke with Mack by telephone and informed him to turn himself into authorities.<ref name=\"MSNBCMack\"/> He also authored an op-ed piece in the Las Vegas Review Journal condemning Mack's actions.<ref>{{cite news | last =Tong | first =Dean | coauthors = | title =Mack Has Failed Fathers Everywhere | newspaper =Las Vegas Review Journal| location = | pages = | language = | publisher = | date =28 June 2006 | url = | accessdate =}}</ref> Tong appeared in the 2007 [[48 Hours (TV series)|CBS 48 Hours Mystery Special]] documenting the events surrounding Darren Mack and the murder of his wife<ref name=\"48hoursDarrenMack\"/> as well as commentary about the case on [[Rita Cosby: Live & Direct]]<ref name=\"MSNBCMack\"/> Tong has made numerous other appearances on national television talk shows, including on [[Dr. Phil (TV series)|Dr. Phil]],<ref name=\"DrPhill\"/> [[Nancy Grace (TV series)|CNN's Nancy Grace]], and [[The Montel Williams Show]].<ref>{{cite video | people =Montel Williams, Dean Tong | title =Abused by My Teacher | medium =Television | publisher =CBS Television | location = | date =24 October 2000 | url = }}</ref>\n\nTong was a media consultant to [[WFTV| WFTV Channel 9]] during the [[Death of Caylee Anthony|trial of Casey Anthony]]<ref>{{cite video | people =Jeff Deal, Dean Tong | title =Casey on Trial | medium =Television News | publisher =WFTV Channel 9 | location = | date =6 June 2011 | url =https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nSklH-9CSo0 }}</ref> and a media consultant for cases such as the [[Eli\u00e1n Gonz\u00e1lez affair]], [[Murder of JonBen\u00e9t Ramsey]], and [[Michael Jackson#2003\u201305: Second child sexual abuse allegations and acquittal|the sexual abuse allegations against Michael Jackson from 2003-05]].<ref name=\"SoutherScribeInterview\"/><ref>{{cite news | last =Thomson | first =Linda | coauthors = | title =Jackson\u2019s Case Unique, Experts Say | newspaper =Desert News | location = | pages = | language = | publisher = | date =15 June 2005 | url =http://www.deseretnews.com/article/600141540/Jacksons-case-unique-experts-say.html?pg=all | accessdate =22 August 2013 }}</ref> He was also a media consultant to ABC News during the [[Kobe Bryant sexual assault case]] in 2003.<ref>{{cite news | last =DuBreuil | first =Jim | coauthors = | title =Does Sex Polygraph Rule Out Child Abuse | newspaper =ABC News| location = | pages = | language = | publisher = | date =16 October 2003 | url =http://abcnews.go.com/Primetime/story?id=132443&page=1 | accessdate =22 August 2013 }}</ref> Tong has also been involved with the [[Florida Legislature]] in relation to the passage of laws to protect children. One such bill, nicknamed the ''Child Spanking Bill'',<ref name=\"SoutherScribeInterview\"/> he assisted Senator Jim Hargrett with the wording for the bill in relation to signs that are consistent with physical child abuse.<ref name=\"SoutherScribeInterview\"/> Tong also played a role with the passage of the ''Malicious False Abuse Law'' and the repeal of the ''Florida Child Abuse Registry''. \n[[File:Dean Tong Signing Autographs.png|thumb|Dean Tong signing autographs at the F.A.C.T. -- Parenting Conference in 2000.]]\nTong is a public speaker and has performed engagements including keynote speaker at FathersDay2000, a rally held in Washington DC to spread awareness of fathers who are not allowed to participate in raising their children.<ref>{{cite news | last =Jenkins | first =Chris | title =For Some Fathers, A Day To Protest | newspaper =The Washington Post| publisher =High Beam Research  | date =19 June 2000| url =http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-520006.html | archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20160415231856/https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-520006.html | url-status =dead | archive-date =15 April 2016 | accessdate =18 August 2013 }}</ref> He has also spoke as part of the [[Children's Rights Council|Children's Rights Council national conference]].<ref>{{cite news | title =April 30 \u2013 May 5, 2001 | newspaper =The Washington Post| publisher =High Beam Research  | date =29 April 2001| url =http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-442069.html | archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20181116193208/https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P2-442069.html | url-status =dead | archive-date =16 November 2018 | accessdate =18 August 2013 }}</ref>\n\nTong is the author of three books and numerous publications on the topic of false abuse allegations. In 1992, Tong published his first book, ''Don't Blame ME, Daddy: False Accusations of Child Sexual Abuse''.<ref name=\"EpicDontBlameMe\">{{cite book | last = | first = | authorlink = | title =Don't Blame ME Daddy: False Accusations of Child Sexual Abuse | work = | publisher =[[Educational Resources Information Center]] | date =1991-11-30 | url =https://archive.org/details/dontblamemedaddy00tong | format = | doi = | accessdate =18 August 2013 | isbn =9781878901293 | url-access =registration }}</ref> It was written after his legal battles to prove his innocence of accusations against him.<ref name=\"SSentinelAuthorSeeks\"/> The book detailed the increase of false accusations of child sexual abuse in relation to divorce and child custody cases.<ref name=\"EpicDontBlameMe\"/> He followed up with the book ''Ashes to Ashes, Families to Dust'' in 1996. The book provided information for those falsely accused of abuse. In 2002, Tong published his third book, ''Elusive Innocence: Survival Guide for the Falsely Accused''.<ref name=\"EOHE\">{{cite journal | last =Finley | first =Gordon | authorlink = | title =Father \u2013 Child Relationships Following Divorce | journal =Encyclopedia of Human Ecology | volume =1: A-H | issue = | pages =291\u2013293 | date = | language = | url = | jstor = | issn = | doi = | id = | mr = | zbl = | jfm = | accessdate = }}</ref> The book, which targeted attorneys, detailed the difference between actual abuse and false accusations of abuse as well as domestic violence allegations.<ref name=\"EOHE\"/><ref name=\"FBJ\">{{cite journal | title =Elusive Innocence: Survival Guide for the Falsely Accused | journal = Florida Bar Journal| date =1 July 2002 | url =http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-88588042.html | archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20160307215858/https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-88588042.html | url-status =dead | archive-date =7 March 2016 | accessdate =18 August 2013}}</ref> It included chapters on fighting false accusations and a summary of case studies involving false accusations.<ref name=\"FBJ\"/> Tong also penned the Foreword to the 2009 book ''I'm Going to be a Dad, Now What?'' written by Craig Baird.<ref name=\"CBIGBAD\">{{cite book | last =Baird | first =Craig | authorlink = | title =I'm Going To Be A Dad, Now What? | publisher =Atlantic Publishing Company | series = | volume = | edition = | year =2009 | location = | pages = | language = | url =https://books.google.com/?id=EIG35IuWGsIC&dq=%22dean+tong%22 | doi = | id = | isbn =9781601383952 | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref>\n\n===Bibliography===\n\n* 2002, ''Elusive Innocence: Survival Guide for the Falsely Accused''<ref name=\"FBJ\"/>\n* 1996, ''Ashes to Ashes, Families to Dust: False Accusations of Child Abuse: A Roadmap for Survivors''\n* 1992, ''Don't Blame ME, Daddy: False Accusations of Child Sexual Abuse''<ref name=\"EpicDontBlameMe\"/>\n\n===Select publications===\n\n* 2012, [http://groundreport.com/sesame-street-and-sex-abuse-clash/  Sesame Street and Sex Abuse Clash], [[Ground Report]]\n* 2007, [https://www.academia.edu/202984/The_Penile_Plethysmograph_Abel_Assessment_for_Sexual_Interest_and_MSI-II_Are_They_Speaking_the_Same_Language The Penile Plethysmograph, Abel Assessment for Sexual Interest and MSI-II: Are They Speaking the Same Language?], The American Journal of Family Therapy \n* 2003, [https://web.archive.org/web/20160319002443/https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1N1-0FF5C3B5ED35128C.html Will Bryant's fame cost his chance for fair trial?], [[Post-Tribune]]\n* [http://fatherhood.about.com/library/weekly/uc031103a.htm  To Err Is Human, Especially in Child Abuse Cases], [[About.com]]\n\n==Personal==\n\nTong has served as the president of VOCAL (Victims of Child Abuse Laws) in the [[Tampa Bay|Tampa Bay area]].<ref name=\"SSentinelAuthorSeeks\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://abuse-excuse.com/ Abuse Excuse - Dean Tong Consultancy Website]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tong, Dean}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American male writers]]\n[[Category:Northeastern University alumni]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Portsmouth]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Writers from Tampa, Florida]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| honorific_prefix          = \n| name                      = Dean Tong\n| honorific_suffix          = \n| native_name               = \n| native_name_lang          = \n| image                     = Dean_Tong.png\n| image_size                = \n| alt                       = \n| caption                   = \n| birth_name                = \n| birth_date                = <!-- {{Birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| birth_place               = \n| disappeared_date          = <!-- {{Disappeared date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (disappeared date the